# General Project Rules

## Package Management
- Use pnpm exclusively (not npm or yarn)
- Run `pnpm install` from root (workspace mode)
- Add dependencies to correct workspace package

## TypeScript
- TypeScript required for all JS code
- Strict mode enabled everywhere
- No `any` types

## Code Style
- No inline comments unless critical for understanding
- Use JSDoc/TSDoc only for public APIs
- Code should be self-documenting
- No TODO comments in committed code

## Documentation
- README.md must be extremely concise — only critical info to work on the project
- Detailed documentation belongs in AGENTS.md
- No verbose explanations — bullet points and code blocks preferred

## Git
- Commit messages: conventional commits format
- Branch naming: `feature/*`, `fix/*`, `deploy/*`
- Never commit secrets or `.env` files

## File Naming
- Components: PascalCase
- Composables/utils: camelCase
- Config files: kebab-case or standard names
- SCSS partials: `_kebab-case.scss`

## Environment
- Node.js 24+ LTS (see `.nvmrc`)
- Use `.env.example` as template, never commit `.env`
